Porcine reproductive and respiratory syndrome, Chile
----------------------------------------------------
Information received on (and dated) 15 Oct 2013 from Dr Victor Ramirez Arias, [Director, Division of Livestock Protection, Agriculture and Livestock Service (SAG), Ministry of Agriculture], Santiago, Chile

Summary
Report type: immediate notification
Date of start of the event: 3 Sep 2013
Date of pre-confirmation of the event: 9 Oct 2013
Report date: 15 Oct 2013
Date submitted to OIE: 15 Oct 2013
Reason for notification: reoccurrence of a listed disease
Date of previous occurrence: 2007
Manifestation of disease: clinical disease
Causal agent: Arterivirus
Nature of diagnosis: clinical, laboratory (basic), laboratory (advanced), necropsy
This event pertains to a defined zone within the country

New outbreaks (1)
Outbreak 1: Maipo [Santiago Metropolitan Region]
Date of start of the outbreak: 3 Sep 2013
Outbreak status: continuing (or date resolved not provided)
Epidemiological unit: farm
Affected animals:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Swine / 8229 / 2554 / 1651 / 0 / 0 /
Affected population: Swine: breeding females and their offspring. Main clinical signs in females: cough, fever, loss of appetite, blue ears, vulvar edema, abortions, premature births, increase of the number of mummified fetuses and birth of weak offspring; in piglets: respiratory distress and diarrhea.

Summary of outbreaks
Total outbreaks: 1
Total animals affected:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Swine / 8229 / 2554 / 1651 / 0 / 0 /
Outbreak statistics:
Species / Apparent morbidity rate / Apparent mortality rate / Apparent case fatality rate / Proportion susceptible animals lost*
Swine / 31.04 percent / 20.06 percent / 64.64 percent / 20.06 percent
*Removed from the susceptible population through death, destruction, and /or slaughter

Epidemiology
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection: unknown or inconclusive
Epidemiological comments: the outbreak is limited to a compartment which corresponds to the population in a single commercial farm. Until the date of this report, there is no evidence of other outbreaks.

Control measures
Measures applied: quarantine; disinfection of infected premises/establishment(s); vaccination prohibited; no treatment of affected animals
Measures to be applied: screening

Diagnostic test results
Laboratory name and type / Species / Test / Test date / Result
Official Laboratory Lo Aguirre (National laboratory) / Swine / antibody detection ELISA / 10 Oct 2013 / Positive
Official Laboratory Lo Aguirre(National laboratory) / Swine / real-time reverse transcriptase / polymerase chain reaction (RRT-PCR) / 15 Oct 2013 / Positive
Laboratory Agrovet (private laboratory) / Swine / antibody detection ELISA / 9 Oct 2013 / Positive
University of Concepcion (private laboratory) / Swine / immunohistochemical test / 11 Oct 2013 / Positive

Future reporting
The event is continuing. Weekly follow-up reports will be submitted.

